Label: Source
Description: Where the information originally came from

Label: Geographic Coordinates
Description: The geographic location represented in a standard format

Label: Database Reference
Description: A link to the same entity in another database

Label: Type
Description: Specifies what kind of thing an entity is

Label: Comment
Description: A human-readable description or annotation

Label: Label
Description: A human-readable name for an entity

Label: See Also
Description: A reference to related information

Label: Is Subtype Of (SDoH)
Description: Shows when one SDoH concept is a more specific type of another SDoH concept

Label: Is Subtype Of (Disease)
Description: Shows when one disease is a more specific type of another disease

Label: Is Subtype Of (Compound)
Description: Shows when one chemical compound is a more specific type of another compound

Label: Is Subtype Of (Environment)
Description: Shows when one environment type is a more specific type of another environment

Label: Part Of (Location)
Description: Shows when one geographic location is contained within another location

Label: Part Of (Compound)
Description: Shows when one chemical structure is a component of a larger compound

Label: Found In (Compound in Location)
Description: Indicates where a specific chemical compound has been detected or is present in a specific geographic area

Label: Found In (Environment in Location)
Description: Indicates where a specific environmental condition or feature exists

Label: Isolated In (Organism in Location)
Description: Shows which country a particular Organisms (bacterial strains) was collected or sampled

Label: Disease Prevalence in Location
Description: How common a disease is in a specific geographic area

Label: SDoH Prevalence in Location
Description: How common a SDoH concept is in a specific geographic area

Label: Disease Mortality in Location
Description: The mortality data or rate of the disease within a specific geographic location

Label: Associates (Disease with Gene)
Description: Shows the association between a disease and a gene

Label: Associates (SDoH with Disease)
Description: Shows the association between a SDoH concept and a disease by analysis on MeSH term co-occurrence in MEDLINE papers

Label: Treats (Compound treats Disease)
Description: Shows that a drug or compound is used to treat a particular disease

Label: Contraindicates (Compound contraindicated for Disease)
Description: Shows that a drug should not be used for a particular disease

Label: Interacts (Compound with Compound)
Description: Shows when two drugs or compounds affect each other when taken together

Label: Upregulates (Compound increases Gene)
Description: Shows that a drug or compound increases the expression of a gene

Label: Downregulates (Compound decreases Gene)
Description: Shows that a drug or compound decreases the activity of a gene

Label: Expressed In (Gene expressed in Disease)
Description: Shows gene expression level in one cancer type or a group of cancer types

Label: Responds To (Organism responds to Compound)
Description: Shows how an organism (bacterial strains) reacts to a drug or chemical

Label: Resistant To (mutantGene resistant to Compound)
Description: Shows when variants of a gene resistant to a drug

Label: Response To (mutantGene response to Compound)
Description: Shows when variants of a gene response to a drug

Label: Adverse Response To (mutantGene adverse response to Compound)
Description: Shows when variants of a gene adversely response to a drug

Label: Positive Marker (Gene marker for Disease)
Description: correlation between mRNA expression of a gene and patient survival of a cancer shows the gene is "prognostic - favorable"

Label: Negative Marker (Gene marker against Disease)
Description: correlation between mRNA expression of a gene and patient survival of a cancer shows the gene is "prognostic - unfavorable"

Label: Resembles (Disease resembles Disease)
Description: Shows the association between two diseases by analysis on MeSH term co-occurrence in MEDLINE papers

Label: Has Role (Compound has biological role)
Description: Describes the biological function or purpose of a chemical compound

Label: Abbreviation
Description: two-letter postal state abbreviation

Label: Activity Sources
Description: Where information about biological activity came from

Label: Antimicrobial Resistance
Description: ability of bacteria to resist the effects of antibiotic drugs

Label: Biovar
Description: A variant of a bacterial species based on biochemical characteristics

Label: City FIPS Code
Description: five-digit number, composed by three-digit county code and two-digit city code to uniquely identify a city in a state

Label: Code
Description: GeoNames code to uniquely identify a geographic location

Label: Collection Date
Description: When a sample was collected

Label: Co-occurrence
Description: the number of articles in which the two terms co-occurred

Label: County FIPS Code
Description: Three-digit number to uniquely identify a county in a state

Label: Data Source
Description: Where the data originally came from

Label: Data Value
Description: The actural value of disease prevalence in a location

Label: Data Value Type
Description: Measurements or statistics used to report the disease prevalence in a location, such as age-adjusted prevalence

Label: Data Value Unit
Description: The units used to measure the data value of disease prevalence in a location, such as percentage

Label: Date
Description: The date related to compound In location, with the type of date defined in Date Type

Label: Date Type
Description: What kind of date used to report compound in location, such as sample collection date, completion date

Label: Drug-Drug Interaction Risk
Description: The potential danger level when two drugs are taken together

Label: Disease
Description: The disease on which the variants of a gene affected by a compound

Label: Domain
Description: The major area of social determinant of health

Label: Enrichment
Description: Statistical measure of how much more common two terms co-occur is than expected

Label: Ensembl ID
Description: A gene's identifier in Ensembl genome database

Label: Fisher's Test
Description: the p-value from Fisher's exact test for whether the observed co-occurrence exceeded that expected by chance

Label: GenBank Accession
Description: A unique identifier for a genetic sequence in the GenBank database

Label: Genome Size
Description: The total amount of genetic material in an organism

Label: Global Health Estimate Code
Description: A standardized code for cause of death category used in WHO reports

Label: Gram Stain
Description: A classification of bacteria based on their cell wall (positive or negative)

Label: Has Antimicrobial Resistance Phenotype
Description: Whether the organism shows resistance or susceptibility to antibiotics

Label: Host Age
Description: The age of the organism from which a sample was collected

Label: Host Gender
Description: The biological sex of the organism from which a sample was collected

Label: Host Health
Description: The health status of the organism from which a sample was collected

Label: Host Is Human
Description: Whether the sample came from a human

Label: Host Name
Description: The name or type of organism from which a sample was collected

Label: Is Resistant
Description: Whether an organism is resistant to a drug or compound

Label: ISO3 Country Code
Description: A three-letter code representing a country

Label: Isolation Country
Description: The country where a sample was collected

Label: Isolation Source
Description: The specific material or environment from which a sample was obtained

Label: Laboratory Typing Method
Description: The technique used to identify or classify a microorganism

Label: Laboratory Typing Platform
Description: The equipment or system used for laboratory identification

Label: Latitude
Description: The north-south position on Earth's surface in degrees

Label: Level
Description: The level of organism in the taxonomy

Label: Location Name
Description: The name of a geographic place

Label: Longitude
Description: The east-west position on Earth's surface in degrees

Label: Lower Bound
Description: The minimum value in a range

Label: Maximum Phase
Description: The furthest stage a drug has reached in clinical trials

Label: Measurement Sign
Description: Indicates whether a value is greater than, less than, or equal to

Label: Measurement Unit
Description: The units used for a measurement

Label: Measurement Value
Description: The numerical result of a measurement

Label: Media
Description: The environment where the compound exists in location, such as air, water, soil

Label: MeSH IDs
Description: A list of  Medical Subject Headings terms an enviroment concept maps to

Label: MeSH List
Description: A list of Medical Subject Headings terms a disease maps to

Label: Method
Description: Measurements or statistics used to report the SDoH prevalence in a location, such as Percentage

Label: Metric Name
Description: Measurements or statistics used to report the disease prevalence in a location, such as Percent

Label: Metrics
Description: Measurements or statistics used to report the compound/environment found in a location, such as maximum concentration, total applied

Label: Mortality Per 100k
Description: mortality rate per 100,000 population

Label: Motility
Description: Whether and how an organism can move

Label: Odds Ratio
Description: A statistical measure of how strongly two terms co-occur

Label: OMIM List
Description: A list of Online Mendelian Inheritance in Man concepts a disease map to

Label: Oxygen Requirement
Description: amount of oxygen an organism needs to survive

Label: Pathovar
Description: A variant of a bacterial species that infects a specific plant host

Label: Percent of Place Area in ZIP
Description: What percentage of a place's area falls within a ZIP code

Label: Percent of ZIP Area in Place
Description: What percentage of a ZIP code's area falls within a place

Label: Phase
Description: The stage of clinical testing for a drug

Label: Population
Description: The number of people living in an area

Label: Resistant Phenotype
Description: The observable resistance characteristics of an organism

Label: Salinity
Description: The salt content of water or environment

Label: Serovar
Description: A variant of a bacterial species based on immune response characteristics

Label: Short Question Text
Description: A brief version of a survey question

Label: SMILES
Description: A text representation of a chemical structure

Label: Sporulation
Description: Whether and how an organism forms protective spores

Label: Standardized SMILES
Description: A normalized text representation of a chemical structure

Label: State
Description: A state or province

Label: State Abbreviation
Description: The two-letter abbreviation for a state

Label: State Description
Description: The full name of a state

Label: State FIPS Code
Description: two-digit number uniquely identify a state

Label: State Name
Description: The full name of a state

Label: Strain
Description: A specific genetic variant of an organism

Label: Synonyms
Description: Alternative names for the same entity

Label: Temperature Range
Description: The range of temperatures in which an organism can grow

Label: Testing Standard Year
Description: The year of the testing standards used

Label: Topic
Description: The topic of the social determinant of health concept

Label: Total Population
Description: The total number of people in an area

Label: Unit
Description: The measurement unit used to describe the values of compound/environment found in a location, such as pound, ug/L

Label: Upper Bound
Description: The maximum value in a range

Label: USA Isolation Country
Description: Whether the sample was collected in the United States

Label: Usability
Description: How suitable or appropriate something is for use

Label: Value
Description: The measured/estimated value of a metric, used in multiple predicates, such as compound/environment found in a location, disease/SDoH prevalence in a location, Mortality in a location

Label: Variable
Description: The measured SDoH concept, some with short description

Label: Vendor
Description: The company or organization that supplied something

Label: Year
Description: The year the data is reported

Label: ZIP Code Type
Description: The type of a ZIP code, such as standard, PO BOX

Label: Social Determinants of Health
Description: Social and economic factors that influence health outcomes

Label: Administrative Area
Description: A geographic region with administrative boundaries like cities or states

Label: Chemical Entity
Description: A chemical substance or compound

Label: Disease
Description: A disorder or illness that affects health

Label: Environmental Feature
Description: An environmental entity, such as environmental quality entity

Label: Gene
Description: A unit of heredity that determines biological characteristics

Label: Organism Taxon
Description: A classification group for living organisms
